sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Change PowerShell Policies to an Insecure Level - PowerShell
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects use of Set-ExecutionPolicy to set insecure policies

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: New Lolbin Process by Office Applications
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: This rule will monitor any office apps that spins up a new LOLBin process. This activity is pretty suspicious and should be investigated.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Vadim Khrykov (ThreatIntel), Cyb3rEng (Rule), Michael Haag, Christopher Peacock @securepeacock (Update), SCYTHE @scythe_io (Update)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application create an instance of one of the office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application'...etc. This can be used by malicious actor to create a malicious office document with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in reference)
